challengeName: Create GUI for Open Molecule Generator
detailedRequirements:
Previously, we have improved the codebase for open molecule generator (OMG) rool (http://sourceforge.net/p/openmg/), the new codebase can be found at https://gitlab.com/katynp/topcoder-omg. Please check the README.md file about how to use the code base for building and testing.

For this challenge, we'd like to create a GUI by using Java Swing for OMG tool similar as PMG_GUI.zip, the UI will be sligtly tweaked as following.

The UI is not required to strictly follow the screen, you can adjust if you think the layout would  be much clearly.

Following are the general requirements.

  1. The title should be "Open Molecule Generator"
  2. "Prescribed Fragment" section is corresponding to '-fr' option if specified.
  3. "Bad list" section is corresponding to '-badlist' option if specified.
  4. "Save output as" is corresponding to '-out' option if specified.
  5. For "Prescribed Fragment" section and "Bad list" section, you can only select existing files, For "Save output as", you can specify new file to save. Please play arround PMG_GUI.zip for behavior checking.
  6. "Elemental Composition" section is mandatory, it is corresponding to the '-ec' option.
  7. The box containding message like "Execution results will be shown here...", will show the output when generating the molecule. It will be clearly beforehand, for each generation.
  8. The number of generated molecules at last, will be shown in Molecule count input box.
  9. When clicking the Start button, it will do some basic validation, like if the Elemental Composition is specified or not etc.
  10. For Stop button, it is used to stop the molecule generating process if the generation takes much times.

The final result should be a JAR containing everything that can be run anywhere, so you are expected to update the build.xml file to add tasks that will generate another JAR file (let's call it as OMG_GUI.jar), which can be run to show the GUI for Open Molecule Generation.
finalSubmissionGuidelines:
• New/Update the Java files and build scripts
  • Updated README.md for the changes.
  • Verification Doc for showcasing the test scenarios
